pr_body:
**This PR is to summarize the work I did during the gsoc and merge it.**

**1. During the gsoc, I completed the UI design of banyandb and the Database page. Its effects are as follows:**

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189611159-e1fcb637-9bd8-4625-bbb6-5c2fb7314e11.png)

**2. On this page, You can do some basic operations.**

- You can right-click on the side directory bar to open the menus of group, stream and measure, and select corresponding operations, as shown below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189612022-8865dfb1-85d4-43f4-a64e-e0e3bb5dfbf7.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189612080-0a1e414c-b3d7-4cf2-83e3-4eb1432733bb.png)

- You will find that the name of the group in the side directory bar is too long to fully display its full name, so I have optimized it; You can hover the mouse, and it will automatically display its full name; You can also control the mouse to long press the right side of the sidebar to customize its width. As shown below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189613295-d8fdcb40-2b2b-4e6d-8ffb-3e5e4d8b3cae.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189613593-6be0c3af-7892-409b-8bdc-2795b1a610cd.png)

- You can also control the width of the sidebar by clicking the top navigation bar button, as shown below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189613839-66ea8d9c-0237-4983-a288-46a91e2caf3f.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189613895-d2b5d55f-87a8-45c8-b7d7-2a3ba07b6db1.png)

- You can click the sidebar menu item to enter the page, as shown below:：

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189614498-3831f75a-f394-4c2d-acf8-07459e60bc80.png)

- You can also open multiple files at the same time, but you need to pay attention to opening up to 9 files; At the same time, you can also click the top navigation to switch the opened files. as shown below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189614989-4a530fbc-e0c6-4d06-b4c9-0d96c5057d7d.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189615064-bc51dd65-8ae4-41d2-ad0b-4bb1ce160e86.png)

- You can click the drop-down box to switch the tag families of the stream. as shown below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189615382-3e632ba5-99a9-4276-8664-9ca9cccd2d5c.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189615542-75abfbaa-d202-4d51-8f14-bbd1e586c192.png)

- You can click the 'open detail' button to open the details of the file. as shown below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189616079-295a5637-b93d-4509-b024-a5df3de9e710.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189616135-1739f26f-465f-4463-85db-fe6a25d4fa41.png)

**3. On this page, You can CRUD a group.**

- You can create a new group. as shown below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189616676-29a6607d-c739-4b52-aac0-116a6c58502d.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189616991-886778cd-6a45-4af0-a115-496da23e6a3f.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189617135-7eba7a25-06b1-4035-84ca-29927016f31a.png)

- You can also edit the group. as shown below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189617354-487f2cfe-44dd-4c7e-9514-76848590a2ec.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189617467-853da086-0a02-415c-b2a6-2dd9dcbe227b.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189617564-01f1ff89-fccb-467c-9899-5d7ed7f93f72.png)

- You can also refresh the group. as shown below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189617797-323919a4-509c-4da0-b204-d53c45995d33.png)

- You can also delete a group：

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189618062-e79dbdff-ba37-4716-8e43-c0ed5f117f34.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189618125-df388f1c-be77-437c-9400-43bd1f7912ad.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189618167-1335def6-d006-4e06-82fd-96eccfc74264.png)

**4. On this page, You can CRUD the stream.**

- You can create a stream. as shown below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189623350-1da96557-0a50-4e8b-9fe5-d5d65e8d390f.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189623443-d1c0e012-0a8b-4498-8b61-f7b4128f598f.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189623553-2a23c510-0529-4aa9-94e5-21bd60ab12cd.png)

- You can click the 'refresh' button to refresh the file. as shown below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189615809-1c482d03-d89b-4fe7-b0eb-09e09c5d3ca0.png)

- You can delete the stream. as shown below:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189623913-53013d70-da0c-4121-aea7-764d2edbdf2a.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189623992-77f27b0c-b533-4e28-bdbb-47e0eec8a480.png)

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/107111186/189624076-2d9cbfc2-745a-4c61-b591-fd27cff3e718.png)


**5. summary**

You will find that there is no editing function in stream; In fact, it may be implemented in the 'open design' button, and it edits the 'tag families' of the stream, because I find that the API can't edit its' Group' and 'name'. Because there is a complex crud of 'tag family' in the stream, I need some time to program it. In the future, I will continue to devote myself to this selfless open source project and continue to make my contributions.

I will upgrade the technology stack first. I plan to use vite + vue3 + element plus to release it in version 0.2.0. Next, I will continue to improve the functions of stream and gradually design and develop measure.

During my time at gsoc, I gained a lot and was very happy to shine on this platform; Let me find the charm of open source, and let me know many very lovely and friendly programmers; Thank you gsoc and Apache community!

Finally, I want to thank my tutors @hanahmily and @kezhenxu94 .Thank you very much for their help and patience in answering the questions I have encountered, which made me adapt to gsoc and understand the open source process specifications very quickly. At the same time, I am also very grateful to the committers and contributors who put forward many sincere suggestions for me during this period! Thank you.
